{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":634,"text":"So if I was to ask you"},{"time":3170,"text":"what the connection between"},{"time":4584,"text":"a bottle of Tide detergent and sweat was,"},{"time":7856,"text":"you'd probably think\nthat's the easiest question"},{"time":9520,"text":"that you're going to be asked\nin Edinburgh all week."},{"time":12300,"text":"But if I was to say\nthat they're both examples"},{"time":14939,"text":"of alternative or new forms of currency"},{"time":18168,"text":"in a hyperconnected,\ndata-driven global economy,"},{"time":21706,"text":"you'd probably think\nI was a little bit bonkers."},{"time":25235,"text":"But trust me, I work in advertising."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27802,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":29835,"text":"And I am going to tell you the answer,"},{"time":31894,"text":"but obviously after this short break."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34504,"text":"So a more challenging question is one"},{"time":36413,"text":"that I was asked, actually,\nby one of our writers"},{"time":38296,"text":"a couple of weeks ago,\nand I didn't know the answer:"},{"time":40797,"text":"What's the world's best\nperforming currency?"},{"time":43037,"text":"It's actually Bitcoin."},{"time":44947,"text":"Now, for those of you\nwho may not be familiar,"},{"time":47162,"text":"Bitcoin is a crypto-currency, a virtual\ncurrency, synthetic currency."},{"time":50620,"text":"It was founded in 2008\nby this anonymous programmer"},{"time":54426,"text":"using a pseudonym Satoshi Nakamoto."},{"time":57294,"text":"No one knows who or what he is."},{"time":59665,"text":"He's almost like the Banksy\nof the Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61926,"text":"And I'm probably not going\nto do it proper service here,"},{"time":65034,"text":"but my interpretation\nof how it works is that"},{"time":67201,"text":"Bitcoins are released\nthrough this process of mining."},{"time":69984,"text":"So there's a network\nof computers that are challenged"},{"time":72532,"text":"to solve a very complex\nmathematical problem"},{"time":74686,"text":"and the person that manages to solve\nit first gets the Bitcoins."},{"time":77952,"text":"And the Bitcoins are released,"},{"time":78938,"text":"they're put into a public\nledger called the Blockchain,"},{"time":81582,"text":"and then they float, so\nthey become a currency,"},{"time":84235,"text":"and completely decentralized,\nthat's the sort of"},{"time":87282,"text":"scary thing about this,\nwhich is why it's so popular."},{"time":89830,"text":"So it's not run\nby the authorities or the state."},{"time":92306,"text":"It's actually managed by the network."},{"time":94383,"text":"And the reason that it's proved\nvery successful"},{"time":96646,"text":"is it's private, it's anonymous,\nit's fast, and it's cheap."},{"time":100064,"text":"And you do get to the point where\nthere's some wild fluctuations with Bitcoin."},{"time":103856,"text":"So in one level it went\nfrom something like 13 dollars"},{"time":106771,"text":"to 266, literally\nin the space of four months,"},{"time":109363,"text":"and then crashed and lost half\nof its value in six hours."},{"time":112102,"text":"And it's currently around that kind of"},{"time":113936,"text":"110 dollar mark in value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116416,"text":"But what it does show\nis that it's sort of gaining ground,"},{"time":119212,"text":"it's gaining respectability."},{"time":120139,"text":"You get services,\nlike Reddit and Wordpress"},{"time":122235,"text":"are actually accepting Bitcoin\nas a payment currency now."},{"time":125530,"text":"And that's showing you that people"},{"time":127473,"text":"are actually placing trust in technology,"},{"time":130024,"text":"and it's started to trump and disrupt"},{"time":132784,"text":"and interrogate traditional institutions"},{"time":134829,"text":"and how we think\nabout currencies and money."},{"time":137568,"text":"And that's not surprising,\nif you think about"},{"time":139016,"text":"the basket case that is the E.U."},{"time":140936,"text":"I think there was a Gallup\nsurvey out recently"},{"time":143151,"text":"that said something like, in America,"},{"time":145137,"text":"trust in banks is at an all-time\nlow, it's something like 21 percent."},{"time":148911,"text":"And you can see here\nsome photographs from London"},{"time":150726,"text":"where Barclays sponsored\nthe city bike scheme,"},{"time":152941,"text":"and some activists have\ndone some nice piece"},{"time":154548,"text":"of guerrilla marketing here\nand doctored the slogans."},{"time":157496,"text":"\"Sub-prime pedaling.\" \"Barclays\ntakes you for a ride.\""},{"time":160993,"text":"These are the more polite ones\nI could share with you today."},{"time":164696,"text":"But you get the gist, so\npeople have really started"},{"time":167149,"text":"to sort of lose faith in institutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169672,"text":"There's a P.R. company called Edelman,"},{"time":171720,"text":"they do this very interesting\nsurvey every year"},{"time":173983,"text":"precisely around trust\nand what people are thinking."},{"time":177178,"text":"And this is a global survey,\nso these numbers are global."},{"time":179920,"text":"And what's interesting\nis that you can see that"},{"time":182183,"text":"hierarchy is having a bit of a wobble,"},{"time":184787,"text":"and it's all about heterarchical now,"},{"time":186573,"text":"so people trust people\nlike themselves more"},{"time":189137,"text":"than they trust corporations\nand governments."},{"time":192221,"text":"And if you look at these figures\nfor the more developed markets"},{"time":194404,"text":"like U.K., Germany, and so on,\nthey're actually much lower."},{"time":197132,"text":"And I find that sort of scary."},{"time":198143,"text":"People are actually\ntrusting businesspeople"},{"time":200215,"text":"more than they're trusting\ngovernments and leaders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203644,"text":"So what's starting to happen,\nif you think about money,"},{"time":206751,"text":"if you sort of boil money\ndown to an essence,"},{"time":208960,"text":"it is literally just an expression\nof value, an agreed value."},{"time":213022,"text":"So what's happening now,\nin the digital age,"},{"time":215142,"text":"is that we can quantify value\nin lots of different ways"},{"time":217884,"text":"and do it more easily,"},{"time":219501,"text":"and sometimes the way\nthat we quantify those values,"},{"time":222179,"text":"it makes it much easier"},{"time":224702,"text":"to create new forms and valid\nforms of currency."},{"time":228499,"text":"In that context, you can see\nthat networks like Bitcoin"},{"time":231555,"text":"suddenly start to make a bit more sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235198,"text":"So if you think we're starting to question"},{"time":238242,"text":"and disrupt and interrogate\nwhat money means,"},{"time":240832,"text":"what our relationship with it\nis, what defines money,"},{"time":243939,"text":"then the ultimate extension of that is,"},{"time":247017,"text":"is there a reason\nfor the government to be in charge"},{"time":249870,"text":"of money anymore?"},{"time":251326,"text":"So obviously I'm looking at this\nthrough a marketing prism,"},{"time":254160,"text":"so from a brand perspective,"},{"time":255830,"text":"brands literally stand or fall\non their reputations."},{"time":259505,"text":"And if you think about it, reputation\nhas now become a currency."},{"time":261832,"text":"You know, reputations are built on trust,"},{"time":263943,"text":"consistency, transparency."},{"time":266493,"text":"So if you've actually decided\nthat you trust a brand,"},{"time":269041,"text":"you want a relationship, you\nwant to engage with the brand,"},{"time":271875,"text":"you're already kind of participating\nin lots of new forms"},{"time":274734,"text":"of currency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276273,"text":"So you think about loyalty."},{"time":278263,"text":"Loyalty essentially is a micro-economy."},{"time":280326,"text":"You think about rewards\nschemes, air miles."},{"time":283561,"text":"The Economist said a few years ago that"},{"time":285710,"text":"there are actually more\nunredeemed air miles in the world"},{"time":289900,"text":"than there are dollar\nbills in circulation."},{"time":292800,"text":"You know, when you are standing\nin line in Starbucks,"},{"time":295348,"text":"30 percent of transactions\nin Starbucks on any one day"},{"time":298058,"text":"are actually being made\nwith Starbucks Star points."},{"time":301120,"text":"So that's a sort of Starbucks currency"},{"time":302954,"text":"staying within its ecosystem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304987,"text":"And what I find interesting is that Amazon"},{"time":307915,"text":"has recently launched Amazon coins."},{"time":310995,"text":"So admittedly it's a currency at the moment\nthat's purely for the Kindle."},{"time":313734,"text":"So you can buy apps and make\npurchases within those apps,"},{"time":316922,"text":"but you think about Amazon,"},{"time":318319,"text":"you look at the trust\nbarometer that I showed you"},{"time":320677,"text":"where people are starting\nto trust businesses,"},{"time":323615,"text":"especially businesses\nthat they believe in and trust"},{"time":326116,"text":"more than governments."},{"time":327506,"text":"So suddenly, you start thinking,"},{"time":329008,"text":"well Amazon potentially could push this."},{"time":330846,"text":"It could become a natural extension,"},{"time":332536,"text":"that as well as buying stuff --"},{"time":334037,"text":"take it out of the Kindle --\nyou could buy books, music,"},{"time":336728,"text":"real-life products, appliances\nand goods and so on."},{"time":341301,"text":"And suddenly you're getting\nAmazon, as a brand,"},{"time":343729,"text":"is going head to head\nwith the Federal Reserve"},{"time":345346,"text":"in terms of how you want\nto spend your money,"},{"time":347513,"text":"what money is, what constitutes money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349888,"text":"And I'll get you back\nto Tide, the detergent now,"},{"time":353484,"text":"as I promised."},{"time":354896,"text":"This is a fantastic article I came\nacross in New York Magazine,"},{"time":357229,"text":"where it was saying that drug\nusers across America"},{"time":360059,"text":"are actually purchasing drugs"},{"time":362235,"text":"with bottles of Tide detergent."},{"time":364886,"text":"So they're going into convenience stores,"},{"time":366974,"text":"stealing Tide,"},{"time":368084,"text":"and a $20 bottle of Tide"},{"time":370278,"text":"is equal to 10 dollars\nof crack cocaine or weed."},{"time":375154,"text":"And what they're saying,\nso some criminologists"},{"time":377417,"text":"have looked at this and they're\nsaying, well, okay,"},{"time":379822,"text":"Tide as a product sells at a premium."},{"time":381648,"text":"It's 50 percent\nabove the category average."},{"time":383765,"text":"It's infused with a very\ncomplex cocktail of chemicals,"},{"time":387093,"text":"so it smells very luxurious\nand very distinctive,"},{"time":389478,"text":"and, being a Procter and Gamble brand,"},{"time":391426,"text":"it's been supported by a lot\nof mass media advertising."},{"time":395026,"text":"So what they're saying is that drug\nusers are consumers too,"},{"time":397895,"text":"so they have this\nin their neural pathways."},{"time":399967,"text":"When they spot Tide, there's a shortcut."},{"time":401896,"text":"They say, that is trust. I trust that.\nThat's quality."},{"time":404653,"text":"So it becomes this unit of currency,"},{"time":407272,"text":"which the New York Magazine described"},{"time":409058,"text":"as a very oddly loyal crime\nwave, brand-loyal crime wave,"},{"time":412555,"text":"and criminals are actually\ncalling Tide \"liquid gold.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":415908,"text":"Now, what I thought\nwas funny was the reaction"},{"time":418123,"text":"from the P&amp;G spokesperson."},{"time":419467,"text":"They said, obviously tried\nto dissociate themselves from drugs,"},{"time":422491,"text":"but said, \"It reminds me of one thing"},{"time":424897,"text":"and that's the value of the brand\nhas stayed consistent.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":428938,"text":"Which backs up my point\nand shows he didn't even"},{"time":430799,"text":"break a sweat when he said that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432636,"text":"So that brings me back\nto the connection with sweat."},{"time":435330,"text":"In Mexico, Nike has run\na campaign recently"},{"time":437669,"text":"called, literally, Bid Your Sweat."},{"time":439443,"text":"So you think about,"},{"time":440832,"text":"these Nike shoes have got sensors in them,"},{"time":442566,"text":"or you're using a Nike FuelBand"},{"time":444067,"text":"that basically tracks\nyour movement, your energy,"},{"time":446748,"text":"your calorie consumption."},{"time":448553,"text":"And what's happening here,\nthis is where you've actually"},{"time":450388,"text":"elected to join that Nike community.\nYou've bought into it."},{"time":453418,"text":"They're not advertising\nloud messages at you,"},{"time":455538,"text":"and that's where advertising\nhas started to shift now"},{"time":457736,"text":"is into things like services,\ntools and applications."},{"time":460390,"text":"So Nike is literally acting\nas a well-being partner,"},{"time":463335,"text":"a health and fitness partner\nand service provider."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466220,"text":"So what happens with this\nis they're saying, \"Right,"},{"time":468378,"text":"you have a data dashboard.\nWe know how far you've run,"},{"time":470974,"text":"how far you've moved, what your calorie\nintake, all that sort of stuff."},{"time":473743,"text":"What you can do is, the more you\nrun, the more points you get,"},{"time":476965,"text":"and we have an auction where\nyou can buy Nike stuff"},{"time":479943,"text":"but only by proving that you've actually\nused the product to do stuff.\""},{"time":483466,"text":"And you can't come into this.\nThis is purely"},{"time":485586,"text":"for the community that are sweating"},{"time":487309,"text":"using Nike products. You\ncan't buy stuff with pesos."},{"time":489944,"text":"This is literally a closed\nenvironment, a closed auction space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494942,"text":"In Africa, you know, airtime has become"},{"time":498343,"text":"literally a currency in its own right."},{"time":500177,"text":"People are used to,\nbecause mobile is king,"},{"time":502280,"text":"they're very, very used\nto transferring money,"},{"time":505125,"text":"making payments via mobile."},{"time":507103,"text":"And one of my favorite examples\nfrom a brand perspective"},{"time":509794,"text":"going on is Vodafone, where, in Egypt,"},{"time":511739,"text":"lots of people make purchases in markets"},{"time":514448,"text":"and very small independent stores."},{"time":516229,"text":"Loose change, small\nchange is a real problem,"},{"time":518655,"text":"and what tends to happen\nis you buy a bunch of stuff,"},{"time":521203,"text":"you're due, say,"},{"time":522188,"text":"10 cents, 20 cents in change."},{"time":524331,"text":"The shopkeepers tend to give\nyou things like an onion"},{"time":526971,"text":"or an aspirin, or a piece of gum,"},{"time":528471,"text":"because they don't have small change."},{"time":530199,"text":"So when Vodafone came\nin and saw this problem,"},{"time":532366,"text":"this consumer pain point, they created"},{"time":533817,"text":"some small change which they call Fakka,"},{"time":535891,"text":"which literally sits and is given"},{"time":537572,"text":"by the shopkeepers to people,"},{"time":539767,"text":"and it's credit that goes\nstraight onto their mobile phone."},{"time":542601,"text":"So this currency becomes\ncredit, which again,"},{"time":544987,"text":"is really, really interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546455,"text":"And we did a survey\nthat backs up the fact that,"},{"time":548765,"text":"you know, 45 percent of people"},{"time":550411,"text":"in this very crucial\ndemographic in the U.S."},{"time":553705,"text":"were saying that they're comfortable using"},{"time":555729,"text":"an independent or branded currency."},{"time":558242,"text":"So that's getting really interesting here,"},{"time":560266,"text":"a really interesting dynamic going on."},{"time":562156,"text":"And you think, corporations"},{"time":563681,"text":"should start taking their assets\nand thinking of them"},{"time":566415,"text":"in a different way and trading them."},{"time":568950,"text":"And you think, is it much of a leap?"},{"time":571410,"text":"It seems farfetched,\nbut when you think about it,"},{"time":574449,"text":"in America in 1860,"},{"time":577167,"text":"there were 1,600 corporations\nissuing banknotes."},{"time":581374,"text":"There were 8,000 kinds\nof notes in America."},{"time":584674,"text":"And the only thing that stopped that,"},{"time":585931,"text":"the government controlled\nfour percent of the supply,"},{"time":588539,"text":"and the only thing that stopped it"},{"time":590183,"text":"was the Civil War breaking out,"},{"time":591876,"text":"and the government suddenly wanted\nto take control of the money."},{"time":594948,"text":"So government, money, war,\nnothing changes there, then."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598590,"text":"So what I'm going to ask is, basically,"},{"time":601445,"text":"is history repeating itself?"},{"time":603840,"text":"Is technology making paper\nmoney feel outmoded?"},{"time":607741,"text":"Are we decoupling money\nfrom the government?"},{"time":609884,"text":"You know, you think about, brands\nare starting to fill the gaps."},{"time":612908,"text":"Corporations are filling gaps\nthat governments can't afford to fill."},{"time":616139,"text":"So I think, you know,\nwill we be standing on stage"},{"time":618900,"text":"buying a coffee -- organic,\nfair trade coffee -- next year"},{"time":622585,"text":"using TED florins or TED shillings?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":625366,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627053,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":629253,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}